abstract: >
  Typed LLM Council is a multi-model deliberation orchestrator with three-layer
  verifier isolation (schema + adapter + content), anti-sycophancy forced verdicts,
  and structured per-stage outputs. v2.3.0 ships the adapter skeleton (Claude /
  Gemini / GPT / Qwen / Grok-stub contributors + Kimi verifier) and a hardened
  Stage 3 Chain-of-Verification (CoVe) verification path; the remaining phases of
  the 9-phase deliberation protocol are documented in the spec and tracked in the
  roadmap.
